t: Psalm 89
Maschil of Ethan the Ezrahite.
I*p will sing of the mercies of the Lord*s for ever: with my mouth will I make known thy faithfulness to all generations.
For*p I have said, Mercy shall be built up for ever: thy faithfulness shalt thou establish in the very heavens.
I*p have made a covenant with my chosen, I have sworn unto David my servant,
Thy*p seed will I establish for ever, and build up thy throne to all generations. Selah.
And*p the heavens shall praise thy wonders, O Lord:*s thy faithfulness also in the congregation of the saints.
For*p who in the heaven can be compared unto the Lord?*s who among the sons of the mighty can be likened unto the Lord?*s
God*p is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints, and to be had in reverence of all them that are about him.
O*p Lord*s God of hosts, who is a strong Lord*s like unto thee? or to thy faithfulness round about thee?
Thou*p rulest the raging of the sea: when the waves thereof arise, thou stillest them.
Thou*p hast broken Rahab in pieces, as one that is slain; thou hast scattered thine enemies with thy strong arm.
The*p heavens are thine, the earth also is thine: as for the world and the fulness thereof, thou hast founded them.
The*p north and the south thou hast created them: Tabor and Hermon shall rejoice in thy name.
Thou*p hast a mighty arm: strong is thy hand, and high is thy right hand.
Justice*p and judgment are the habitation of thy throne: mercy and truth shall go before thy face.
Blessed*p is the people that know the joyful sound: they shall walk, O Lord,*s in the light of thy countenance.
In*p thy name shall they rejoice all the day: and in thy righteousness shall they be exalted.
For*p thou art the glory of their strength: and in thy favour our horn shall be exalted.
For*p the Lord*s is our defence; and the Holy One of Israel is our king.
Then*p thou spakest in vision to thy holy one, and saidst, I have laid help upon one that is mighty; I have exalted one chosen out of the people.
I*p have found David my servant; with my holy oil have I anointed him:
With*p whom my hand shall be established: mine arm also shall strengthen him.
The*p enemy shall not exact upon him; nor the son of wickedness afflict him.
And*p I will beat down his foes before his face, and plague them that hate him.
But*p my faithfulness and my mercy shall be with him: and in my name shall his horn be exalted.
I*p will set his hand also in the sea, and his right hand in the rivers.
He*p shall cry unto me, Thou art my father, my God, and the rock of my salvation.
Also*p I will make him my firstborn, higher than the kings of the earth.
My*p mercy will I keep for him for evermore, and my covenant shall stand fast with him.
His*p seed also will I make to endure for ever, and his throne as the days of heaven.
If*p his children forsake my law, and walk not in my judgments;
If*p they break my statutes, and keep not my commandments;
Then*p will I visit their transgression with the rod, and their iniquity with stripes.
Nevertheless*p my lovingkindness will I not utterly take from him, nor suffer my faithfulness to fail.
My*p covenant will I not break, nor alter the thing that is gone out of my lips.
Once*p have I sworn by my holiness that I will not lie unto David.
His*p seed shall endure for ever, and his throne as the sun before me.
It*p shall be established for ever as the moon, and as a faithful witness in heaven. Selah.
But*p thou hast cast off and abhorred, thou hast been wroth with thine anointed.
Thou*p hast made void the covenant of thy servant: thou hast profaned his crown by casting it to the ground.
Thou*p hast broken down all his hedges; thou hast brought his strong holds to ruin.
All*p that pass by the way spoil him: he is a reproach to his neighbours.
Thou*p hast set up the right hand of his adversaries; thou hast made all his enemies to rejoice.
Thou*p hast also turned the edge of his sword, and hast not made him to stand in the battle.
Thou*p hast made his glory to cease, and cast his throne down to the ground.
The*p days of his youth hast thou shortened: thou hast covered him with shame. Selah.
How*p long, Lord?*s wilt thou hide thyself for ever? shall thy wrath burn like fire?
Remember*p how short my time is: wherefore hast thou made all men in vain?
What*p man is he that liveth, and shall not see death? shall he deliver his soul from the hand of the grave? Selah.
Lord,*p where are thy former lovingkindnesses, which thou swarest unto David in thy truth?
Remember,*p Lord, the reproach of thy servants; how I do bear in my bosom the reproach of all the mighty people;
Wherewith*p thine enemies have reproached, O Lord;*s wherewith they have reproached the footsteps of thine anointed.
Blessed*p be the Lord*s for evermore. Amen, and Amen.
